  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Boil a full kettle</p><p>Add your <strong>farfalle</strong> to a pot of boiled water with a large pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook the farfalle for 8-10 min or until cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once done, drain the farfalle</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1610452908410-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1610452908410-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1610452908410-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1610452908410-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1610452908410-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Chop your<strong> chives</strong> and <strong>parsley</strong> finely, including the stalks</p><p>Cut your <strong>lemon[s]</strong> into quarters</p><p>Combine the <strong>chopped garlic </strong>with <strong>half </strong>of the <strong>chopped herbs</strong>, a squeeze of <strong>lemon </strong>juice<strong> </strong>and 25g <span class=\"text-purple\">[40g]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[50g]</span><strong> butter</strong> – this is your <strong>garlic & herb butter</strong></p><p>Tip: Put the butter in the microwave for 10 secs if it's too cold to mix!</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1610453184929-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1610453184929-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1610453184929-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1610453184929-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1610453184929-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Top, tail and chop your<strong> courgette[s]</strong> in half lengthways, then into batons</p><p>Dissolve your <strong>chicken stock mix </strong>in 200ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[260ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [350ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>and stir in your <strong>soft cheese </strong>– this is your <strong>creamy stock</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1610453193514-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
